1 lowed the actual and necessary expenses incurred by them in the performance of their duties.
2 (7) Each member of the board shall have an official institutional electronic mail address
3 that is posted on a publicly available website for the board.
4 SECTION 2. The amendments to ORS 341.283 by section 1 of this 2026 Act become oper-
5 ative 90 days following the effective date of this 2026 Act.
6 SECTION 3. ORS 341.275 is amended to read:
7 341.275. [(1) The board shall be composed of seven members.]
8 [(2) No person who is an employee of the community college district shall be eligible to serve as a
9 member of the board for the district by which the employee is employed.]
10 (1) The board shall be composed of seven voting members and at least one nonvoting
11 member who is a student enrolled in at least six in-person credits per term, other than a
12 summer term, at a community college in the district.
13 (2) A nonvoting member who is a student must be:
14 (a) Elected or selected through a process held by the student government or student
15 governance structure at a community college in the district;
16 (b) Permitted to vote ceremonially on any question subject to a vote of the board, with
17 the vote entered along with the yeas and nays in the journal of the board under ORS 341.283;
18 (c) Permitted to participate in any meeting, discussion or function of the board, excluding
19 an executive session; and
20 (d) Provided any information distributed to voting members of the board.
21 (3) A person may not serve on the board of a specific community college district if the
22 person is an employee of the district.
23 SECTION 4. The amendments to ORS 341.275 by section 3 of this 2026 Act become oper-
24 ative on July 1, 2027.
25 SECTION 5. ORS 341.283, as amended by section 1 of this 2026 Act, is amended to read:
26 341.283. (1) After July 1 of each year, the board of a district shall meet and organize by electing
27 a chairperson and a vice chairperson from its voting members.
28 (2) The board shall provide for the time and place of its regular meetings, at any of which it
29 may adjourn to the next succeeding regular meeting or to some specified time prior thereto. Special
30 meetings shall be convened by order of the chairperson of the board or upon the request of four
31 voting board members at least 24 hours before such meeting is to be held, or by common consent
32 of the voting board members. Notice of any special meeting shall be given to [the] all members
33 pursuant to bylaws of the board.
34 (3) A majority of the voting board members shall constitute a quorum. The affirmative vote of
35 the majority of voting members of the board is required to transact any business.
36 (4) The board shall adopt rules for the government of the conduct of its members and its pro-
37 ceedings. The board shall keep a journal and, on the call of any one of its voting members, shall
38 cause the yeas and nays to be taken and entered upon its journal upon any question before it.
39 (5) Any duty imposed upon the board as a body shall be performed at a regular or special
40 meeting and shall be made a matter of record. The consent to any particular measure obtained from
41 individual board members when the board is not in session shall not be an act of the board and shall
42 not be binding upon the district.
43 (6) Members of the board shall receive no compensation for their services, but they shall be al-
44 lowed the actual and necessary expenses incurred by them in the performance of their duties.
45 (7) Each member of the board shall have an official institutional electronic mail address that is
