1 posted on a publicly available website for the board.
2 SECTION 6. The amendments to ORS 341.283 by section 5 of this 2026 Act become oper-
3 ative on July 1, 2027.
4 SECTION 7. Each community college district shall submit a report that includes dis-
5 cussion of the degree to which the community college has complied with the requirements
6 of ORS 341.275 and 341.283, as amended by sections 1 and 3 of this 2026 Act, to the interim
7 committees of the Legislative Assembly related to higher education not later than September
8 1, 2028. The report under this section must include input from representatives of student,
9 faculty and nonfaculty staff governance organizations.
10 SECTION 8. ORS 341.335 is amended to read:
11 341.335. (1) The board shall declare the office of a board member vacant if it finds any of the
12 following:
13 (a) The incumbent has died or resigned.
14 (b) The incumbent has been removed or recalled from office or the election of the incumbent
15 thereto has been declared void by the judgment of a court.
16 (c) The incumbent has ceased to be a resident of the district from which the incumbent was
17 nominated or elected.
18 (d) The incumbent has ceased to discharge the duties of office for two consecutive months unless
19 prevented therefrom by sickness or other unavoidable cause or unless excused by the chairperson
20 of the board.
21 (2) A board member who is nominated or elected by zone and who changes permanent residence
22 from one zone of a district to another zone or who by a change in zone boundaries no longer resides
23 in the zone of nomination or election is entitled to continue to serve as board member until June
24 30 following the next regular district election at which a successor shall be elected by the electors
25 to serve for the remainder of the unexpired term, if any. The successor shall take office July 1 next
26 following the election.
27 (3) When a vacancy is declared under subsection (1) of this section, and the vacancy occurs
28 not less than 90 days before the regular district election for the position, the remaining board
29 members shall meet and appoint a person to fill the vacancy from any of the electors of the district
30 not more than 90 days after the vacancy occurs, if the position is one filled by both nomination
31 and election at-large, and otherwise from any of the electors of the zone from which the vacancy
32 occurs.
33 (4)(a) If the offices of a majority of the board members are vacant at the same time, the gov-
34 erning body of the principal county shall appoint persons to fill the vacancies from any of the
35 electors of the district if the positions are filled by both nomination and election at-large, and oth-
36 erwise from any of the electors of the zone from which the vacancy occurs.
37 (b) If the remaining board members fail to appoint a person to fill a vacancy in accord-
38 ance with subsection (3) of this section:
39 (A) For at-large seats, the governing body of the county with the most electors in the
40 district shall appoint a resident of the district within the county to fill the vacancy; and
41 (B) For a zone seat for which there is a vacancy, the governing body of the county with
42 the most electors in the zone shall appoint a resident of the zone who is within the county.
43 (c) A governing body described in paragraph (b) of this subsection shall make an ap-
44 pointment under this subsection not more than 14 days following the failure of the board to
45 fill a vacancy.
