1 (5) The period of service of a board member appointed under subsection (3) or (4) of this section
2 commences upon appointment and expires June 30 next following the next regular district election
3 at which a successor is elected. The successor shall be elected to serve the remainder, if any, of the
4 term for which the appointment was made. If the term for which the appointment was made expires
5 June 30 after the election of the successor, the successor shall be elected to a full term. In either
6 case, the successor shall take office on July 1.
7 SECTION 9. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
8 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
9 on its passage.
